  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Remote support DRR-Team scoping mission (light) South Sudan 2022</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There have again been severe floodings in South Sudan (November 2021). The Bentiu region was one of the affected regions which had to deal with heavy floods. The main Bentiu refugee camp has been supported years ago with the design and construction of a drainage system through the Dutch embassy and has therefore not been affected, however the smaller refugee settlements have been affected as well as the surrounding areas. Floodings are a recurrent problem and a long term issue in South Sudan. The next rainy season is already due in April 2022. Due to climate change more floodings have occurred since 2019. The regional/local government is in charge of the region of Bentiu. The refugee settlements are managed by actors like IOM, WFP and UNMISS who have also been involved with the effects of the floods. In cooperation with the local authorities the humanitarian actors have been working at immediate needs (short term/ medium term measures) to deal with the current situation after the floods. However, an integrated solution is required for the region including the refugee settlements. DRR-Team support has been requested, to work towards an integrated solution, with a focus on midterm and longer term perspectives which can be implemented in the reality of South Sudan.</narrative>
  </description>
